caption.text: From a late afternoon photowalk with @moctedamus...I can honestly say that Pro HDR is worth the $2 bucks it costs (I spend twice as much on my daily Venti Americano at any rate)...this HDR mashup was created out of a single image edited on qBro, using Pro HDR's Library HDR feature...this means the possibilities are endless ppl...for example you can over expose one image, save, underexpose the same image, save, then merge them using Pro HDR...you don't have to worry about having blurry images on your end result, as camera shake is taken out of the equation doing it this way...I believe you can use the same technique with contrast and saturation...this was my first attempt with this technique...I hope you like it...
